
C2Call ([tpl]IPAc-en|icon|ˈ|s|iː|t|uː|k|aʊ|l|[/tpl]) GmbH, German startup, which provides an array of Web calling applications, offers a dynamic multitude of browser-based JAVA[tpl]cite web|last=Collier|first=Suzanne|title=Press Release: C2Call's FriendCaller Introduces Java-based Hassle-Free Video conferencing|Video Calling]]|url=http://www.marketwire.com/press-release/c2calls-friendcaller-introduces-java-based-hassle-free-video-calling-1535410.htm|publisher=Marketwire.com|accessdate=May 7, 2012[/tpl] Voice over Internet Protocol VoIP solutions for the computing cloud.[tpl]cite web|title=Browser-based JAVA VoIP Solution|url=http://c2call.com/|publisher=c2call.com|accessdate=11 June 2012[/tpl] One of the pioneers in Internet protocol providers’ industry, C2Call extends the possibilities of connectivity apps for smartphones, Internet browsers and SIP clients.[tpl]cite web|title=FriendCaller is SIP compatible|url=http://www.pcworld.com/appguide/app.html?id=608989&expand=false|publisher=PCworld|accessdate=12 June 2012[/tpl] A person-to-person VoIP service provider based in Germany, C2Call GmbH offer users a simple, affordable and effective alternative to existing VoIP communication tool.[tpl]cite web|title=A Modern, Multi Platform, VoIP Communication Tool|url=http://tech2.in.com/news/apps/friendcaller-is-a-multiplatform-voip-solution/292932|accessdate=11 June 2012[/tpl]

==History==

C2Call was founded in 2008 by CEO, Martin Feuerhahn and CTO, Michael Knecht.[tpl]cite web|title=C2Call Founded in 2008|url=http://buzzsparks.org/c2call|publisher=buzzsparks.org|accessdate=15 June 2012[/tpl] Prior to establishing C2Call, Martin and Michael founded Actai in 2004.[tpl]cite web|title=Actai Founded in 2004|url=http://actai.com/|publisher=Actai.com|accessdate=15 June 2012[/tpl] The purpose of Actai was to develop mobile content solutions for Mobile Network Operators and Internet Media companies.[tpl]cite web|title=Actai Services|url=http://actai.com/Services.html|publisher=Actai.com|accessdate=15 June 2012[/tpl] Actai’s customers included Germany’s largest MVNO, Aldi Talk and one of Germany’s largest ISPs, the Freenet AG.
In May 2008, they spun off C2Call to incorporate C2Call GmbH in Werl, Germany. Transferring all related IP to C2Call GmbH to prepare it for external funding and international expansion.
In February 2009, C2Call introduced FriendCaller [tpl]cite web|title=C2Call Launched FriendCaller|url=http://techcrunch.com/2012/04/18/hey-remember-friendcaller-it-just-launched-7-way-mobile-video-chat/|publisher=Techcrunch.com|accessdate=12 June 2012[/tpl] into the digital communications marketplace, earning instant recognition for its innovative contribution to the ever-changing social networking industry.

===Operation===

C2Call works on the principles of Java by temporarily loading a Java widget into Internet browsers such as Internet Explorer, Mozilla Firefox, Opera, Safari, Chrome and other browsers that support Javascript.[tpl]cite web|last=Collier|first=Suzanne|title=Press Release: C2Call's FriendCaller Introduces Java-based Hassle-Free Video conferencing|Video Calling]]|url=http://www.marketwire.com/press-release/c2calls-friendcaller-introduces-java-based-hassle-free-video-calling-1535410.htm|publisher=Marketwire.com|accessdate=June 15, 2012[/tpl] The widget adds VoIP functions to the browser.[tpl]cite web|title=FriendCaller supported Platforms|url=http://blog.tmcnet.com/blog/tom-keating/voip/c2call-new-browserbased-java-voip-app.asp|publisher=tmcnet|accessdate=15 April 2012[/tpl] and is compatible with leading operating systems like Windows, Linux, and Macintosh
Unlike other VoIP-based telephony services, there is no software to download, install and configure.[tpl]cite web|title=No Software to download, Install or Reconfigure|url=http://www.tmcnet.com/scripts/reprint.aspx?PagePrint=http://www.tmcnet.com/usubmit/2008/04/15/3388451.htm|publisher=tmcnet.com|accessdate=31 May 2012[/tpl] The browser-based Internet phone, FriendCaller WebPhone,[tpl]cite web|title=FriendCaller WebPhone|url=http://www.wiwo.de/technologie/valley-talk-angriff-auf-skype/5691194.html|publisher=wiwo.de|accessdate=11 June 2012[/tpl]  lets the user experience next generation VoIP technology with Group Video Calling, without having the need for any pre-requisite software installation.[tpl]cite web|title=No Need Of Software Installations|url=http://voip.about.com/od/servicesandsolutions/gr/FriendCallerReview.htm|publisher=About.com|accessdate=11 June 2012[/tpl] FriendCaller iPhone and Android apps demonstrate the unique capabilities to start a web phone and establish a peer-to-peer connection through any Internet browser without prerequisite installations.C2Call is a venture-backed company that has generated more than $2 million in revenue since April 2010.[tpl]cite web|title=Generated more than 2 Million revenue|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/prnewswire/press_releases/2010/08/05/AQ45883|publisher=bizjournals|accessdate=31 May 2012[/tpl] 
After perfecting FriendCaller’s VoIP platform, C2Call GmbH applied a great deal of time and resources toward constructing ensured network compatibility with a wide array of standard and mobile computing devices. Individuals who own Apple Inc products such as the iPhone, iPad, and iPod Touch can enjoy the same connective perks built into FriendCaller’s browser-based version, as well as the service’s VoIP downloadable version from Appstore and Google Play.

==C2Call's Products and Services==

For those who place the bulk of their phone calls from home or work computers, C2Call GmbH’s WebPhone version complies with all browser-powered VoIP protocol. FriendCaller’s WebPhone can be permanently saved on almost any desktop computer free of charge. Users can have 7-Way Cross-platform Mobile Video Chat in real time with up to 27 people.[tpl]cite web|title=First multi-point 7-way group video calling app for smartphone platforms|url=http://www.marketwatch.com/story/friendcaller-continues-to-revolutionize-mobile-and-browser-based-communications-with-the-introduction-of-7-way-group-video-calling-from-c2call-2012-04-18|publisher=marketwatch.com|accessdate=1 May 2012[/tpl][tpl]cite web|last=Collier|first=Suzanne|title=Press Release: Introduction of 7-Way Group Video Calling From C2Call|url=http://www.marketwire.com/press-release/friendcaller-continues-revolutionize-mobile-browser-based-communications-with-introduction-1645525.htm|publisher=Marketwire.com|accessdate=26 April 2012[/tpl]
C2Call GmbH’s FriendCaller for Android operating systems and iOS Operating System allow users to experience the power of Mobile Group Video Calling.[tpl]cite web|title=7-Way Mobile Group Video Chat|url=http://techcrunch.com/2012/04/18/hey-remember-friendcaller-it-just-launched-7-way-mobile-video-chat/|publisher=techcrunch|accessdate=11 June 2012[/tpl] Manufactured by companies like Motorola and HTC, Google-supported Android smart phones can easily download FriendCaller in the form of a free application, facilitating cost-effective calling to contacts across the country and around the world.[tpl]cite web|title=Cheap Call Rates Across the World|url=http://blog.friendcaller.com/celebrate-66th-national-italian-republic-day-with-cheapest-calls-guaranteed/|publisher=blog.friendcaller.com|accessdate=15 June 2012[/tpl] 
Users of Android, iPhone, iPod touch and iPad earn free calling credits by watching a short video or downloading their favorite apps with "OfferWall" feature available for all iOS [tpl]cite web|title=Free Credits form iOS OfferWall|url=http://blog.friendcaller.com/short-tutorial-to-earn-free-calling-credits-on-iphone/|publisher=FriendCaller blogs|accessdate=26 April 2012[/tpl] and Android devices.[tpl]cite web|title=Free credits form Android OfferWall|url=http://blog.friendcaller.com/low-on-credits-how-about-getting-some-for-free-from-android-offerwall/|publisher=FriendCaller blogs|accessdate=26 April 2012[/tpl]
People who own a Nokia S40 device can make the most of FriendCaller as well.[tpl]cite web|title=FriendCaller on Nokia S40|url=http://blog.friendcaller.com/out-now-friendcaller-on-nokia-s40-devices/|publisher=blog.friendcaller.com|accessdate=15 June 2012[/tpl] The Nokia Series 40 provides users with a set-up wizard for navigating the installation process,[tpl]cite web|title=FriendCaller uses SIP technology|url=http://blog.friendcaller.com/now-possible-friendcaller-sip-over-other-applications/|publisher= FriendCaller.com|accessdate=15 June 2012[/tpl] although C2Call gives users the choice of foregoing set-up wizard assistance prior to making calls with FriendCaller SIP.[tpl]cite web|title=FriendCaller SIP clients|url=http://www.friendcaller.com/en/enterprise/sip-clients.html|publisher= FriendCaller.com|accessdate=1 May 2012[/tpl]
C2Call GmbH’s FriendCaller is also compatible with Facebook, the world’s largest social networking site.[tpl]cite web|title=FriendCaller for Facebook App|url=http://blog.friendcaller.com/why-should-you-use-friendcaller-facebook-app/|publisher=blog.friendcaller.com|accessdate=15 June 2012[/tpl] Clients can use this app directly from their Facebook account without downloading and installation hazard. FriendCaller Facebook App shows compatibility with Facebook Connect.[tpl]cite web|title=Facebook Connect Compatibility|url=http://blog.friendcaller.com/start-2011-with-the-new-improved-friendcaller-app-for-your-android/|publisher=FriendCaller Blogs|accessdate=30 April 2012[/tpl] Users can login to FriendCaller using their Facebook credentials. FriendCaller's Facebook VoIP app takes the hassle out of inviting friends to join C2Call’s VoIP network, offering a host of benefits beyond FriendCaller’s highly affordable communication solutions. 
The unique CallMe-Link,[tpl]cite web|title=CallMe-Link|url=http://www.zdnet.com/blog/btl/mobile-voip-services-no-longer-taboo-following-at-t-news/25585|publisher=Zdnet|accessdate=15 June 2012[/tpl] allow others to make instant calls to FriendCaller users within their Internet browsers. The link can be embedded into emails, shared via social networks and can be sent as an instant message by copying the HTML or BBCode. Users can also integrate as a badge in Outlook Signature. To start the conversation with FriendCaller users, non-FriendCaller users only have to click this link.[tpl]cite web|title=Usage of CallMe-Link|url=http://blog.friendcaller.com/how-to-call-a-friend-using-callme-link/|publisher=FriendCaller Blogs|accessdate=27 April 2012[/tpl]
Available either free or at a cost of as low as only two cents per minute for overseas connection. C2Call’s VoIP platform allows users to place local and international phone calls from their homes or offices, saving 80 to 90 percent in comparison to fees charged by traditional phone companies.[tpl]cite web|title=Rates and Pricing|url=http://www.friendcaller.com/en/help/rates-and-pricing.html|publisher=FriendCaller.com|accessdate=12 June 2012[/tpl]

==Funding and Financial Services==

Draper Investment Company proudly supports Germany-based startup C2Call GmbH,[tpl]cite web|title=Draper Investment contribution towards C2Call|url=http://draperinvestmentcompany.wordpress.com/2011/11/21/the-draper-investment-company-portfolio-about-c2call-gmbh-and-voip-technology/|publisher=Draper Investment Company|accessdate=11 June 2012[/tpl] whose FriendCaller service provides an accessible way to communicate between subscribers, as well as those with landlines and mobile devices.[tpl]cite web|title=FriendCaller - An All-In-One VoIP Communication Tool|url=http://draperinvestmentcompany.wordpress.com/2011/06/24/groundbreaking-developments-in-online-communication-c2call-gmbh%E2%80%99s-friendcaller-com-22/|publisher=Draper Investment Company|accessdate=11 June 2012[/tpl] 
The Draper Investment Company portfolio has followed VoIP since near its inception, demonstrating the company’s enthusiasm for IT ventures. Draper Investment Company invested in C2Call GmbH and various other VoIP-savvy companies due to the investor’s belief that VoIP will likely one day eclipse the more traditional telephony methods.[tpl]cite web|title=Modern Communication Tool|url=http://draperinvestmentcompany.wordpress.com/2011/06/24/groundbreaking-developments-in-online-communication-c2call-gmbh%E2%80%99s-friendcaller-com-12/|publisher=Draper Investment Company|accessdate=11 June 2012[/tpl] 
To foster growth of C2Call’s FriendCaller service, the company raised more than $2 million [tpl]cite web|last=HA|first=Anthony|title=Press Release: C2Call raises $2Milllion|url=http://www.nytimes.com/external/venturebeat/2010/08/06/06venturebeat-c2call-raises-2m-to-spread-calls-across-the-79945.html|publisher=nytimes|accessdate=15 June 2012[/tpl] in funding during the early months of 2010 - A funding from Original Skype investor Bill Draper of Draper Investment Company [tpl]cite web|title=Draper Investment Company|url=http://www.draperco.com/|publisher=Draper Investment Company|accessdate=26 April 2012[/tpl] High-Tech Grunderfonds and Klaus Wecken, co-founder of KHK Software (now taken over by Sage Group)

==C2Call's Environmental Record==

C2Call has been making efforts to minify their impact on the environment and has all its working operated under green technology powered servers.
C2Call hopes to manufacture products that will better protect the environment and save energy.

